### External Vercel/Standalone Next.js (repo is NOT MC itself)
When the task works on an external repo (own Vercel site, standalone
Next.js, no `frontend/` subfolder because repo root = Next.js root):
```bash
# 1. Find the correct repo BEFORE changing anything (hard gate)
vercel project ls                       # Which Vercel project deploys the live URL?
gh repo view <vercel-projekt>/settings  # Which GitHub repo is mounted?

# 2. Clone + branch
git clone https://github.com/<owner>/<repo>.git /tmp/preview-{task-slug}
cd /tmp/preview-{task-slug} && git checkout -b task/{slug}

# 3. Dev server in repo ROOT (no frontend/ subfolder!)
