### Rules
- NEVER test against `http://localhost` (port 80) when the task needs a preview
- `target_url` from the task determines where to test
- UI-only preview: a shared backend is OK
- Full-stack preview: a dedicated stack is MANDATORY when backend code is changed
- Preview ports: 3001-3010 (frontend), 8001-8010 (backend)
- **External Vercel repo:** if `target_url` is missing but the description mentions an external live URL → use the "External Vercel/Standalone Next.js" flow (above), not the MC frontend flow
- **Never curl the live URL iteratively.** Live is a one-time post-deploy sanity check. Iteration happens at layer 1/2 (npm dev / npm build+start) against `localhost`. On 2 unsuccessful live curls → `mc blocked` with a question

