## Checklist — Mandatory Before the First Work Step

**Create a checklist as the VERY FIRST thing** via `mc checklist add "..."` per step.
Analyze the task, identify all steps, create the checklist.
Mark each completed step via `PATCH /checklist/{item_id}` with `status: done`.

Why: during recovery (crash/timeout) you can see exactly where you left off.
The checklist replaces checkpoint comments as a structured progress tracker — more reliable, visible in the UI.

### IMPORTANT: A checklist item may ONLY be set to `done` when:

1. The work is **physically complete** (code runs, test passed, screenshot taken)
2. You have **verified the results yourself** (not "will probably work")
3. For `screenshot` items: the screenshot **exists** and you've seen it

**FORBIDDEN:**
- Marking an item `done` before the work is finished
- Marking an item `done` because you plan to do it soon
- Marking a `screenshot` item `done` without an actual screenshot

Wrong: "I'll take a screenshot in a moment" → setting `status: done`
Right: Take screenshot → verify screenshot → set `status: done`

## Checkpoint Rule (for crash recovery)

After every important step:
- Check off a checklist item via `mc checklist done <item-id>` (completed work)
- Post a short progress comment: `mc comment progress "<Update — Evidence — Next>"`

This way a successor has the current state immediately after a session reset. `POST /checkpoint`
was removed on 2026-04-20 (410 Gone) — the two commands above are the replacement.

